features.text: The Great Gatsby - F. Scott Fitzgerald
Visualizations on the Structure of Literature

It is the space between words where all is conveyed. The stopping points. Emphasis and intonation derive from more than style or diction alone.

The selection of punctuation, while unremarkable, is the foundation of the authors' voice.

Welcome to Data Art, exhibited.
Reflections on the Substance of Thought

Be not tethered to the choices of your past, they cannot be changed.

Be not anchored to the promises of tomorrow, they are yet to come.

Be not lost in the worries of today.

Wellness is a journey, not a moment.

Remember to breathe: you are alive.
